![Ping test result](https://github.com/rayann2004/aws-restart-journey/blob/main/networking/image.png?raw=true)


1. Created the VP)
   - Name: `Test VPC`
   -IPv4 CIDR: `192.168.0.0/18`

2. Created a Public Subnet
   - Name: `Public Subnet`
   -IPv4 CIDR: `192.168.1.0/26`
   - Associated it with the Test VPC.

3. Created a Route Table
   - Name: `Public Route Table`
   - Associated it with the `Public Subnet`.
   - Added route:
     - Destination: `0.0.0.0/0`
     - Target: Internet Gateway (IGW)

4. Created and Attached an Internet Gateway
   - Name: `IGW-Test-VPC`
   - Attached it to the `Test VPC`.

5. Configured Network ACL
   - Name: `Public Subnet NACL`
   - Inbound Rule: Allow all traffic (`0.0.0.0/0`)
   - Outbound Rule: Allow all traffic (`0.0.0.0/0`)

6. Configured Security Group

   -Name: `Public Security Group`
   - Description: Allows public access
   -Inbound Rules:
     - SSH (22) → Anywhere
     - HTTP (80) → Anywhere
     - HTTPS (443) → Anywhere
   -Outbound: All traffic allowed

7. Launched EC2 Instance

   - AMI: Amazon Linux 2023
   - Type: `t3.micro`
   - Subnet: Public Subnet
   - Auto-assign Public IP: Enabled
   - Security Group: Public Security Group
   - Key Pair: `vockey`

8. Connected via SSH
9. Tested Internet Connectivity
   ping google.com

   Successful replies received — internet access confirmed.


